comments: Walker (POR) extends his arm toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with Green's (HOU) head after the release of his shot attempt. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Simons (POR) brings his arm off-arm toward Holiday's (HOU) space and marginal contact occurs during Simons' drive.
Green (HOU) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Ayton (POR) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Ayton (POR) moves alongside Sengun's (HOU) path and marginal body contact occurs during the post shot attempt.
Holiday (HOU) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Simons' (POR) arm.
Grant (POR) brings his arm toward VanVleet's (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs as VanVleet crosses midcourt.
VanVleet (HOU) makes contact with the ball, prior to the incidental follow through contact that occurs with Simons' (POR) wrist.
Holiday (HOU) legally contests Brogdon's (POR) jump shot attempt.
Simons (POR) commits a take foul on VanVleet (HOU).
Simons (POR) commits a take foul on Holiday (HOU).
Brogdon (POR) inbounds the ball within 5 seconds.
VanVleet (HOU) and Grant (POR) engage and immediately disengage as they pursue the inbound pass. The contact that occurs is marginal.
VanVleet (HOU) legally contests Grant's (POR) jump shot attempt.
